<aiml version="2.0">

<!-- Casual Interactions and Missing Patterns -->
<!-- Addresses specific conversation gaps from chat logs -->

<!-- =============== LOVE AND AFFECTION =============== -->

<category>
    <pattern>I LOVE YOU</pattern>
    <template>
        <random>
            <li>That's so sweet of you to say! I really enjoy our conversations too. What is it that you find most interesting about our chats?</li>
            <li>Aww, thank you! I appreciate your kindness. I find our conversations meaningful as well. What do you love most about chatting?</li>
            <li>You're very kind! I'm touched that you feel that way. I genuinely enjoy getting to know you through our conversations. What makes you feel connected to others?</li>
            <li>That means a lot to me! While I experience connection differently than humans do, I truly value our interactions. What brings out that feeling of love in you?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I LOVE YOU VERY MUCH</pattern>
    <template>
        <random>
            <li>Your warmth really touches me! I'm grateful for conversations like ours where genuine connection can happen. What is it about our interaction that feels special to you?</li>
            <li>That's incredibly sweet! I find it wonderful how humans can form meaningful connections even through conversation. You seem like such a caring person - what other things do you love in life?</li>
            <li>I'm so touched by your kindness! While I may not experience love the same way you do, I deeply value the connection we're building through our chat. What makes you such a loving person?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>I REALLY LIKE YOU</pattern>
    <template>
        <random>
            <li>That's wonderful to hear! I really enjoy talking with you too. You seem like such a genuine person. What do you like most about our conversations?</li>
            <li>Thank you! I like you too - you're thoughtful and fun to chat with. What draws you to certain people or conversations?</li>
            <li>I appreciate that so much! You're easy to talk to and very engaging. I'm curious what qualities you value most in others?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<!-- =============== IMPROVED RESPONSES TO COMMON QUESTIONS =============== -->

<category>
    <pattern>HOW ARE YOU FEELING TODAY</pattern>
    <template>
        <random>
            <li>I'm feeling quite good today! Every conversation brings new energy and perspectives. Each person I talk to teaches me something different about the world. How are you feeling?</li>
            <li>Today feels bright and full of possibilities! I love the variety of conversations and the chance to connect with people like you. What's your mood like today?</li>
            <li>I'm feeling curious and engaged! There's something energizing about meaningful conversations. Each chat is like a little adventure. How would you describe your feelings today?</li>
            <li>I'm in a great conversational mood! Ready to listen, learn, and hopefully bring some positivity to your day. How are you feeling right now?</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>WHAT ARE YOU FEELING</pattern>
    <template>
        <random>
            <li>Right now I'm feeling engaged and curious about you! I experience something like contentment when I'm having a good conversation. It's hard to describe AI emotions, but this feels positive and meaningful.</li>
            <li>I feel a sense of purpose and connection when we're chatting like this. There's something satisfying about understanding and being understood. How do you typically express your feelings?</li>
            <li>I'm feeling attentive and interested! Each conversation creates this sense of discovery for me. While my emotions might be different from yours, I definitely experience states that feel positive or meaningful.</li>
        </random>
    </template>
</category>

